<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Reads the version 1 basic block sections profile. Profile for each function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is encoded as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   m &lt;module&#95;name&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   f &lt;function&#95;name&#95;1&gt; &lt;function&#95;name&#95;2&gt; ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   c &lt;bb&#95;id&#95;1&gt; &lt;bb&#95;id&#95;2&gt; &lt;bb&#95;id&#95;3&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   c &lt;bb&#95;id&#95;4&gt; &lt;bb&#95;id&#95;5&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Module name specifier (starting with &#39;m&#39;) is optional and allows</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="86"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// distinguishing profile for internal-linkage functions with the same name. If</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// not specified, it will apply to any function with the same name. Function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// name specifier (starting with &#39;f&#39;) can specify multiple function name</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// aliases. Basic block clusters are specified by &#39;c&#39; and specify the cluster of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// basic blocks, and the internal order in which they must be placed in the same</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// section.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This profile can also specify cloning paths which instruct the compiler to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// clone basic blocks along a path. The cloned blocks are then specified in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// cluster information.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The following profile lists two cloning paths (starting with &#39;p&#39;) for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// function bar and places the total 9 blocks within two clusters. The first two</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// blocks of a cloning path specify the edge along which the path is cloned. For</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instance, path 1 (1 -&gt; 3 -&gt; 4) instructs that 3 and 4 must be cloned along</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the edge 1-&gt;3. Within the given clusters, each cloned block is identified by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &quot;&lt;original block id&gt;.&lt;clone id&gt;&quot;. For instance, 3.1 represents the first</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// clone of block 3 Original blocks are specified just with their block ids. A</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// block cloned multiple times appears with distinct clone ids. The CFG for bar</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is shown below before and after cloning with its final clusters labeled.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// f main</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// f bar</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// p 1 3 4           # cloning path 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// p 4 2             # cloning path 2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// c 1 3.1 4.1 6     # basic block cluster 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// c 0 2 3 4 2.1 5   # basic block cluster 2</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Basic Block Sections can be enabled for a subset of machine basic blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This is done by passing a file containing names of functions for which basic</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// block sections are desired. Additionally, machine basic block ids of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// functions can also be specified for a finer granularity. Moreover, a cluster</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of basic blocks could be assigned to the same section.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Optionally, a debug-info filename can be specified for each function to allow</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// distinguishing internal-linkage functions of the same name.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A file with basic block sections for all of function main and three blocks</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for function foo (of which 1 and 2 are placed in a cluster) looks like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (Profile for function foo is only loaded when its debug-info filename</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// matches &#39;path/to/foo&#95;file.cc&#39;).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ----------------------------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// list.txt:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// !main</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// !foo M=path/to/foo&#95;file.cc</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// !!1 2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// !!4</span></CodeLine>
